-- Fortescue Metals Says It Doesn't See Downturn in Chinese Iron Ore Demand
-- Jason Scott
-- 2010-08-03T03:03:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-03/fortescue-metals-says-it-doesn-t-see-downturn-in-chinese-iron-ore-demand.html

          
          
             Fortescue Metals Group Ltd.,
Australia’s third-biggest producer of iron ore, said it doesn’t
see any downturn in demand for iron ore from China. The company
is still talking to investors about rasing money to fund its
expansion projects, Fortescue Chief Executive Officer Andrew
Forrest told reporters at the Diggers and Dealers conference in
Kalgoorlie, Western Australia, today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
